{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f11f71f8-0ba8-41ad-ac9e-e483cb7404c8","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # verify SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # confirm it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso check your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references should be bumped to their **11.x** versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e3bbad1a-360c-4402-abea-c4342c9286cb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"E01B:3EF0C4:73A3E05:8062CAF:69F406BC"},"id":"5f4c87dc-7c49-414c-a49c-ad1c00357f2d","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:49:55.799Z","parentId":"d3f99f71-628c-46d2-a822-31553bbd3bc4"}
